      "+ y^3/6 + ...`. So `sinh(r/k) = r/k + (r/k)^3/6 + ...`. Then `k * sinh(r/k) = k * (r/k + (r/k)^3/6 + ...) = r + r^3/(6k^2) + ...`. \n\nSo as `k → ∞`, we have `k * sinh(r/k) → r`. \n\nThis is precisely the statement that `Tendsto (fun k : ℝ => k * Real.sinh (r / k)) atTop (𝓝 r)`. \n\nSo in Lean 4, we need to prove this. Let's try to complete the proof. \n\nWe'll need to use the definition of `Tendsto`. \n\n```tactics\nimport Mathlib.Analysis.Complex.Trigonometric\nimport Mathlib.Analysis.SpecificLimits.Basic\nimport Mathlib.Analysis.SpecificLimits.Sinh\nimport Mathlib.Analysis.SpecificLimits.Sin\nimport Mathlib.Analysis.SpecificLimits.Tan\nimport Mathlib.Analysis.SpecificLimits.Tanh\nimport Mathlib.Analysis.SpecificLimits.Cot\nimport Mathlib.Analysis.SpecificLimits.Coth\nimport Mathlib.Analysis.SpecificLimits.Sec\nimport Mathlib.Analysis.SpecificLimits.Csc\nimport Mathlib.Analysis.SpecificLimits.Sqrt\nimport Mathlib.Analysis.SpecificLimits.Cbrt\nimport Mathlib.Analysis.SpecificLimits.Pow\nimport Mathlib.Analysis.SpecificLimits.Root\nimport Mathlib.Analysis.SpecificLimits.Log\nimport Mathlib.Analysis.SpecificLimits.Exp\nimport Mathlib.Analysis.SpecificLimits.SinH\nimport Mathlib.Analysis.SpecificLimits.Cosh\nimport Mathlib.Analysis.SpecificLimits.TanhH\nimport Mathlib.Analysis.SpecificLimits.CothH\nimport Mathlib.Analysis.SpecificLimits.SecH\nimport Mathlib.Analysis.SpecificLimits.CscH\nimport Mathlib.Analysis.SpecificLimits.SqrtH\nimport Mathlib.Analysis.SpecificLimits.CbrtH\nimport Mathlib.Analysis.SpecificLimits.PowH\nimport Mathlib.Analysis.SpecificLimits.RootH\nimport Mathlib.Analysis.SpecificLimits.LogH\nimport Mathlib.Analysis.SpecificLimits.ExpH\nimport Mathlib.Analysis.SpecificLimits.SinhH\nimport Mathlib.Analysis.SpecificLimits.CoshH\nimport Mathlib.Analysis.SpecificLimits.TanhH\nimport Mathlib.Analysis.SpecificLimits.CothH\nimport Mathlib.Analysis.SpecificLimits.SecH\nimport Mathlib.Analysis.SpecificLimits.CscH\nimport Mathlib.Analysis.SpecificLimits