So, for large `k`, `r / k` is small. Thus, `sinh(r / k) ≈ r / k + (r / k)^3 / 6 + ...`.

Then, `k * sinh(r / k) ≈ k * (r / k + (r / k)^3 / 6 + ...) = r + k * (r / k)^3 / 6 + ... = r + r^3 / (6 * k^2) + ...`.

