This establishes the equality that allows us to rewrite the expression.

Now we can rewrite the function in terms of `Real.sinh(r/k) / (1/k)`. As `k` approaches infinity, `1/k` approaches 0, and `r/k` approaches 0. `Real.sinh(x)` can be approximated by `x + x^3/6 + ...`, so `Real.sinh(r/k) ≈ r/k + (r/k)^3/6 + ...`. Therefore, `Real.sinh(r/k) / (1/k) ≈ (r/k + (r/k)^3/6 + ...) / (1/k) = r + r^3/(6k^2) + ...`. As `k` approaches infinity, this approaches `r`.

